  "instructions": [
    "heat the olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat.",
    "add the garlic and onion and cook until softened, about 3 minutes.",
    "add the pecan nuts and cook for an additional 2 minutes.",
    "stir in the peanut butter, lemon juice, salt, and black pepper.",
    "add the chicken broth and bring to a boil.",
    "reduce heat to low and simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes.",
    "stir in the feta cheese and cook for an additional 2 minutes.",
    "serve hot, garnished with fresh thyme if desired.",
    "this dish is best served immediately, as the fermented pecan nuts will lose their flavor if refrigerated or frozen."
